      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Theoretically, yes, devices could analyze voice pitch or ambient room temperature to infer stress levels, but major companies like Google and Amazon heavily guard user privacy with strict policies against building detailed emotional surveillance. Currently, no legitimate smart home ecosystem is capable of tracking your specific feelings with precision enough to violate your trust or sell that data without explicit consent. While the technology for basic biometric inputs exists, the ethical safeguards and lack of profitable utility mean this specific scenario of covert emotional monitoring is highly unlikely in practice.",
