      "content": "Your experience sounds unsettling because while companies claim they won't track emotional states, it is often difficult to audit complex AI systems for hidden background processes that might inadvertently learn from your routine. It is plausible that these systems are reacting to patterns you already exhibit, such as consistently raising the temperature when stressed or dimming lights when anxious, rather than actually detecting a new emotion in real-time. This raises a valid concern about data transparency, as many consumers are unaware of how specific logs or algorithmic adjustments are actually stored and shared. It is essential to check your device settings for privacy modes or request full access logs to verify exactly what your system is seeing and doing behind the scenes.",
